<use f='linux-4.18.y/kernel/livepatch/core.c' l='579' u='c' c='force_store'/>
<def f='linux-4.18.y/kernel/livepatch/transition.c' l='628' ll='644' type='void klp_force_transition()'/>
<doc f='linux-4.18.y/kernel/livepatch/transition.c' l='619'>/*
 * Drop TIF_PATCH_PENDING of all tasks on admin&apos;s request. This forces an
 * existing transition to finish.
 *
 * NOTE: klp_update_patch_state(task) requires the task to be inactive or
 * &apos;current&apos;. This is not the case here and the consistency model could be
 * broken. Administrator, who is the only one to execute the
 * klp_force_transitions(), has to be aware of this.
 */</doc>
